Sentencas: Porous composite cathodes including (La0.74Bi0.10Sr0.16)MnO3-delta (LBSM) and Bi1.4Er0.6O3 (ESB) were fabricated and characterized using AC impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Improvement of (La0.74Bi0.10Sr0.16)MnO3-Bi1.4Er0.6O3 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In our earlier work, the growth and aggregation of ESB particles were found in LBSM-ESB composite cathodes.
Titulo: Improvement of (La0.74Bi0.10Sr0.16)MnO3-Bi1.4Er0.6O3 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, therefore, two approaches were used to restrain the growth and aggregation of ESB particles.
Titulo: Improvement of (La0.74Bi0.10Sr0.16)MnO3-Bi1.4Er0.6O3 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: First, the sintering temperature of the composite cathode was reduced by introducing a sintering function layer, which caused a 22% reduction in the initial polarization resistance (R), but the cathode polarization resistance decreased at a rate of 2.15 x 10-4 Omega cm(2) h(-1) at 700 degrees C during a period of 100 h. Second, nano-sized Gd-doped ceria powder (CGO) was added to the composite cathode system.
Titulo: Improvement of (La0.74Bi0.10Sr0.16)MnO3-Bi1.4Er0.6O3 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Stability improvement was achieved at 10 vol% CGO, and the degradation rate at 700 degrees C was 4.01 x 10(-5) Omega cm(2) h(-1) during a period of 100 h. (C) 2008 Elsevier B.V.
Titulo: Improvement of (La0.74Bi0.10Sr0.16)MnO3-Bi1.4Er0.6O3 composite cathodes for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
